The paper deals with the study of degrees of freedom in a multiple-input single-output (MISO) broadcast channel (BC) with alternating channel state information at the transmitter (CSIT). This involves information theory (cs.IT) as well as networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also uses optimization techniques (cs.MM) and communication and information theory (cs.CE) to analyze the DoF region.
